Here is custom implementation with desired behavior.  

Fork each element (unlike `Spliterators.spliteratorUnknownSize`) progressively (there is only single unprocessed `ForkJoinTask` in the work queue when worker pool is saturated).  
There is only single thread which `trySplit` at any point of time hence there is no atomicy implication for `Iterator.hasNext` and `Iterator.next` and concurrent thread safetiness of the iterator implementation.  
There should be at least one element on the beginning.

**Usage**

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        stream(Spliterators.spliteratorUnknownSize(IntStream.range(0, 10).iterator(), Spliterator.CONCURRENT), true).forEach(SpliteratorTest::process);
        out.println(&quot;---&quot;);
        stream(new ForkNextSpliterator&lt;&gt;(IntStream.range(0, 10).iterator()), true).forEach(SpliteratorTest::process);
    }
    
    private static void process(Integer i) {
        LockSupport.parkNanos(TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS.toNanos((int) (Math.random() * 100)));
        out.println(i + &quot;\t&quot; + currentThread().getName());
    }

**Output**

	0	ForkJoinPool.commonPool-worker-9
	1	ForkJoinPool.commonPool-worker-9
	2	ForkJoinPool.commonPool-worker-9
	3	ForkJoinPool.commonPool-worker-9
	4	ForkJoinPool.commonPool-worker-9
	5	ForkJoinPool.commonPool-worker-9
	6	ForkJoinPool.commonPool-worker-9
	7	ForkJoinPool.commonPool-worker-9
	8	ForkJoinPool.commonPool-worker-9
	9	ForkJoinPool.commonPool-worker-9
	---
	5	ForkJoinPool.commonPool-worker-13
	4	ForkJoinPool.commonPool-worker-4
	0	main
	2	ForkJoinPool.commonPool-worker-2
	7	ForkJoinPool.commonPool-worker-15
	6	ForkJoinPool.commonPool-worker-6
	1	ForkJoinPool.commonPool-worker-9
	3	ForkJoinPool.commonPool-worker-11
	9	ForkJoinPool.commonPool-worker-1
	8	ForkJoinPool.commonPool-worker-8

**Implementation**

    import static java.lang.Long.MAX_VALUE;
    import static java.util.stream.Stream.empty;
    import static java.util.stream.StreamSupport.stream;

    public class ForkNextSpliterator&lt;T&gt; implements Spliterator&lt;T&gt; {
    
        public static &lt;T&gt; Stream&lt;T&gt; parallelStream(Iterable&lt;T&gt; iterable) {
            Iterator&lt;T&gt; iterator = iterable.iterator();
            return iterator.hasNext() ? stream(new ForkNextSpliterator&lt;&gt;(iterator), true) : empty();
        }
    
        private final Iterator&lt;T&gt; iter;
        private final T value;
        private boolean split;
    
        public ForkNextSpliterator(Iterator&lt;T&gt; iter) {
            this.value = iter.next();
            this.iter = iter;
        }
    
        @Override
        public boolean tryAdvance(Consumer&lt;? super T&gt; action) {
            action.accept(value);
            return false;
        }
    
        @Override
        public Spliterator&lt;T&gt; trySplit() {
            return (split ^= true) &amp;&amp; iter.hasNext()
                    ? new ForkNextSpliterator&lt;&gt;(iter)
                    : null;
        }
    
        @Override
        public long estimateSize() {
            return MAX_VALUE;
        }
    
        @Override
        public int characteristics() {
            return CONCURRENT;
        }
    }

