Your `Pojo` class is a parameter to a controller method. Spring will map the web request to your parameter (i.e. `Pojo`).
Injected instances are _not_ beans, but are constructed and bound to your request parameters for each request. They are not registered in the application context.

For instance, the following code would return &quot;Gonen&quot; when requesting `http://localhost/greet?name=Gonen`:

```
class Pojo {
    private String name;
    public String getName() { return name; }
    public void setName(final String name) { this.name = name; }
}

@RestController
class MyController {
    @GetMapping(&quot;/greet&quot;)
    String greet(Pojo pojo) {
        return pojo.getName();
    }
}
```

* https://docs.spring.io/spring-framework/docs/current/reference/html/web.html#mvc-ann-requestmapping
* https://docs.spring.io/spring-framework/docs/current/reference/html/web.html#mvc-ann-modelattrib-methods

